AGI - Slovak Prime Minister Robert Fico was wounded by firearms and the attacker was arrested. The prime minister was taken to the hospital. The Slovak press agency Tasr reports it.
The attack occurred at the end of a government meeting in Hadlova. According to local newspaper Dennik, Fico came out to greet the crowd when gunshots were fired. The premier was transferred to a hospital in Bratislava by helicopter. An eyewitness saw wounds in the chest and head.&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2 The premier "grave in life danger"</h2>
The Slovak premier, Robert Fico, "is in danger of life". It has announced in a note the office of the same head of government, published on its official Facebook page.<br> According to the statement, Fico will be transported by plane to the Banska Bystrica hospital, as transport to the capital Bratislava would take "too long" and the need for an "emergency intervention". "The next few hours will be decisive," concludes the brief note.
<h2> The area of the attack
The area in front of the House of Culture in Handlova, where the government meeting was held after which Prime Minister Robert Fico was wounded by gunshots, is currently evacuated. The Slovak agency Tasr reports that the attacker was arrested.
<h2> Parliament session suspended
The Slovak Parliament suspended the sitting in the light of Prime Minister Robert Fico's wound in an attack on gunshots at Handlova. This was announced by Parliament's deputy speaker, Lubos Blaha, cited by the local information site Dennikn.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2> President "condemns the attack" to Premier Fico</h2>
The Slovak president, Zuzana Caputova, "condemned the attack firmly" to the Prime Minister, Robert Fico. The spokesman of Head of State Martin Strizinec, cited by the national media.&nbsp;
&nbsp;

