AGI - President Joe Biden has proposed to his challenging two television debates > in June and September, and Donald Trump has immediately accepted. In the space of a few minutes American politics reached the goal that millions of voters expected: see the two candidates challenge themselves live > after launching hard distance attacks. Biden's campaign has given Trump what he's been asking for months, provided that managing the event is not a party organization, and setting a set of conditions.
&nbsp;
The novelty is also in the choice of dates: June > arrives ahead of the dates proposed by the electoral commission dealing with presidential debates. The goal is to convince voters well before September, when all over the country will begin the procedures of the early vote >, by post or through the delivery of envelopes with the card in the prepared boxes. Election Day, the classic election day with the vote in the seats, is scheduled on November 5th.
&nbsp;
However, the Biden campaign asked for some guarantees. The Democrats want the debate to be hosted in a television studio, with microphones that are automatically silenced if one of the duel shows the time available. And they want the comparison to be done in a space where there are only the two challengers and the moderator, without noisy audiences, and without the participation of the third candidate, the novax and independent Robert Kennedy Jr.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp; The proposal indicates how Biden wants to confront Trump on the themes, without offering his rival the weapon of populism >, and everything is done in an aseptic context, in which the risks are calculated. What has been presented today is the first formal offer and is signed by President of the President's campaign, Jennifer O'Malley Dillon. The letter was sent to the committee dealing with presidential debates. In the document it is stated that Biden will not participate in the three debates proposed by the Committee: on 16 September, 1 and 9 October. In his response to the offer, Trump said he wants more than two debates and in "big places", accusing Biden of "being afraid of the crowds".
&nbsp;
Trump aims to inflame the voters live, Biden speaking to them in an aseptic context. O'Malley Dilloni proposed that the first debate be held at the end of June, when the trial in New York had already been completed, where Trump was charged. The date would come immediately after the G7 summit to which Biden will participate and from which, probably, could come with some news to offer voters and regarding international scenarios, beginning with the conflict between Russia and Ukraine. The second debate, proposes the president of the Biden campaign, should be organized "at the beginning of September, with the start of the autumn season of the campaign, soon enough to influence the early vote". This kind of vote was decisive for Biden's victory in 2020.
&nbsp;
Traditionally, Democratic voters are those who choose the system of early vote, considered more complicated, because &nbsp; it is a matter of filling complex forms, a practice that the Middle Republican elector does not love. At the moment Trump drives the polls in most key states, considered those that swing once right and once left, and which were decisive in the 2020 elections.&nbsp;

