AGI - Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky has canceled all the upcoming international travels, in light of the new Russian offensive in the north-eastern region of Kharkiv. L>o announced its press officer, Sergiy Nykyforov, specifying that the leader of Kiev " gave instructions so that all international events planned for the next days are postponed and the new dates are coordinated".&nbsp; Kiev sent further reinforcements to the region. He announced the president's office, underlining that Zelensky "he listened to the report of Chief of Staff Anatoliy Bargylevych.
&nbsp;
Further forces are deployed and there are reserves." &nbsp;The Ukrainian army > announced that it has withdrawn from some areas of the northern front &nbsp;> in the region, where Russia launched an offensive on May 10. "In some areas, near Lukyantsi and Vovchansk, in response to enemy fire and an infantry assault, our units have manoeuvred in the direction of more favorable positions to save the lives of our soldiers and avoid losses," declared the Ukrainian Major State on social media, however ensuring that "the battle continues". &nbsp;

